		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform2><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=17094"><span id=Sage>Kneesmasher</span></a><b><span id=Sage><br>Sage</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>397 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.80]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Well, okay, not much else I can say but to agree with those who stated you should work on your 2-hs NOW! As in...RIGHT NOW!!&nbsp;&nbsp;You don't have to use 2-hs exclusively, but you do need to keep it on par with your 1-hs abilities. The sooner you start on this, the better off you will be. Even if you have to go fight different mobs to work on it, do it!! It is very important in the long run and there are times when 2-hs is just better against the mob. And you might as well work on those BLUNT skills while you're at it!<br><br>I do disagree however with the Anon poster who stated that 1-hs is not needed when you reach level 29 (it's actually level 30) and get stun as a spell. While stun is a GREAT spell and is one I keep loaded at all times regardless of who I'm fighting, the recast time is too slow alone to interupt all the caster's spells. In other words, you may interupt one, but you won't be able to recast stun again before the mob can recast after the interuption.  Stun just isn't that fast.<br><br>Since Casters become one of the most serious threats to your health and well-being as you move up in levels, I ALWAYS use 1-hs/shield when I know I will be encountering casters so I can not only stun, but can also bash to interupt. If you time them right, you can interupt with a stun spell, then wait and watch, interupt with a bash, then wait, by this time you can cast stun again, and if done perfectly it is possible to take on a powerful mob, like a Festering Hag or a Soul Seductress and take her down without her even getting a spell off! Now that's easier said than done but it is something to strive for. If going into Mistmoore, take your 1-hs. The Casters are especially nasty here and if you rely solely on Stun you will miss every other cast and get nuked to the ground. Just a word of warning.<br><br>With your cash availability you should be able to pick up a nice 2-hs. If you want something cheap AND good, it's hard to beat an Axe of the Iron Back, but if you are truly cash-rich, something like Deepwater Harpoon would be better and a Xalgoz or Mithril 2-hs would be considerably better than that! And if you are just ROLLING in plat, then a Nathsar or an Arbitors Combined Greatsword or something along those lines would be the way to go, but they are way out my reach. But if you are just looking for a good, cheap, efficient 2-hs, the Axe of the Ironback is a great little weapon, and since you will be hindered by the damage cap until you reach level 20 anyway, no since investing in something expensive unless you've just got the cash to spare.<br><br>JMHO<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>36th Circle of Dwarven Paladins<br>Twilight Brethren<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
